<HEADLINE> Anti-Flood Chief Chairs Meeting in Hubei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINGZHOU, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier and Head of the
State Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters Wen Jiabao has
urged provinces along the Yangtze River to make strenuous efforts
to protect the Yangtze embankments and win an overall victory over
the floods, the worst since 1931.
</P>
<P>
The essence of the central leadership's instruction is to
ensure the safety of the Yangtze embankments and the lives of the
people, he said.
</P>
<P>
The national anti-flood chief made this remark Tuesday while
presiding over a meeting in Jingzhou City in central China's
Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
He also urged that the flood victims be taken care of and
provided with food, drinking water and housing as well as
security. Criminal activities of various kinds must be dealt with
to maintain social stability in the flooded areas, he said.
</P>
<P>
In related developments, water levels on the Yangtze, as well
as in Dongting and Poyang lakes, have been receding gradually as the
year's fourth flood crest passes down the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a major flood has begun to devastate the country's
northeastern areas including Heilongjiang Province and the Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region, prompting the State Flood Control and
Drought Relief Headquarters to issue an emergency call to
reinforce the battle against the floods in that part of the
country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
