<HEADLINE> Kenya Dismantles Islamists' Network Before Attack: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- A French expert on international
terrorism said Tuesday that Kenya dismantled an Islamists' network
in the region of Mombasa two or three months ago.
</P>
<P>
Professor Xavier Raufer said in an interview with France 2
television channel that France was following that operation by the
Kenyan security force because the terrorists could launch attacks
on French installations in neighboring Djibouti.
</P>
<P>
He regretted that the Islamists, who he said followed the
movement led by Saudi billionaire Oussama Ben Laden, finally
succeeded in making the double bombing attack on U.S. embassies in
Nairobi and Dar es Salaam last week.
</P>
<P>
"There was a space of vague threat which turned around in the
region and which ended by concretizing itself,"said Raufer, who
is a professor of the Institute of Criminology of Paris.
</P>
<P>
He said that the terrorists used Semtex, an extremely powerful
explosive, in attacking the U.S. embassy in Nairobi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
