<HEADLINE> Nepali Leaders Express Condolences Over Loss </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Nepali leaders on Tuesday sent
messages of condolence to Chinese leaders over the huge loss of
lives and property caused by heavy floods in the southern and
eastern parts of China.
</P>
<P>
The official RSS news agency said that in a message to Chinese
President Jiang Zemin, Nepali King Birendra said, "We are saddened
to learn of the considerable loss of lives and property."
</P>
<P>
He extended deep sympathies and condolences to Jiang and
through him to the members of the affected families, RSS said.
</P>
<P>
In a message to his Chinese counterpart, Zhu Rongji, Prime
Minister Girija Prasad Koirala said, "I am grieved to learn about
the huge loss of lives and property... The people and government
of Nepal join me in extending our heartiest condolences to your
excellency and through you to the affected families."  
</P>
