<HEADLINE> Top Chinese Lawmaker Concerned with Flooding in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the National
People's Congress Standing Committee Li Peng called the State
Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters Tuesday evening,
inquiring about the flooding situation in the Nenjiang River in
northeast China.
</P>
<P>
He urged local people to fight the flooding according to the
anti-flood law and further reinforce the river embankment to
protect the major cities along the river such as Harbin.
</P>
<P>
Li also asked the localities to make necessary anti-flood
preparations and timely evacuate the flood-stricken victims to
safe places.
</P>
<P>
Breaches occurred Tuesday in the Nenjiang River Basin in
northeast China's Heilongjiang Province and the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Relief goods and soldiers have been sent to rescue thousands of
local people trapped by floodwaters. 
</P>
