<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Group of 21 Urges Establishment of Committee on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Group of 21 has called for
the establishment of a subsidiary committee to deal with nuclear
disarmament after the Conference on Disarmament (CD) decided here
Tuesday to set up an ad hoc committee on the prohibition of
production of fissile material for nuclear purposes.
</P>
<P>
"The G-21 emphasizes that nuclear disarmament is the highest
priority for the Conference on Disarmament," the group said in a
statement released here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"An ad hoc committee should be established in the CD to
commence negotiations on a phased program of nuclear disarmament
for the complete elimination of nuclear weapons with a specified
framework of time, including a nuclear weapons convention," said
the statement.
</P>
<P>
The group said it put much emphasis on the "elimination of the
possibility of nuclear war and the threats derived from the
continued existence of nuclear weapons, and the use or threat of
use of nuclear weapons."
</P>
<P>
It expressed the hope that the proposed treaty dealing with
fissile material must constitute a nuclear disarmament measure,
and not only a nuclear non-proliferation measure, and be an
integral step leading to the total elimination of nuclear weapons.
</P>
</TEXT>
