<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin to Visit Egypt Early Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin is
scheduled to pay an official visit to Egypt in the first quarter
of next year for political dialog with Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
Egypt's Middle East News Agency Tuesday quoted Russian Charge
d'Affairs here as saying that the two leaders will discuss, among
other things, the issue of establishing a just and durable peace
in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
He said this issue is given top priority by the Russian foreign
policy.
</P>
<P>
Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov will visit Egypt to
prepare for Yeltsin's Cairo visit and consult with his Egyptian
counterpart Amr Moussa on the latest developments of the
deadlocked Mideast peace march, the Russian diplomat said.
</P>
<P>
He said that Russia, a co-sponsor of the Arab-Israeli peace
process, fully supports a Franco-Egyptian initiative on holding an
international conference to rescue the dying peace process.
</P>
<P>
"Moscow has greatly and positively welcomed the Egyptian-French
initiative as having been identical to Moscow's vision on the need
to coordinate endeavors to salvage the flagging peacemaking in the
Middle East," he added.
</P>
<P>
Moscow sees it that the Madrid conference principles,
especially the land-for-peace formula, should be applied in order
to achieve an Arab-Israeli overall settlement, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Russian diplomat added that Moscow works in parallel with
Washington in this field and denied any intention, on the part of
Russia, of competition with the U.S..
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin's forthcoming visit to Egypt is a reciprocal one to
Mubarak's trip Moscow in September last year. Primakov, a Mideast
expert, has visited Egypt twice since 1996.
</P>
<P>
Russia is a co-sponsor together with the U.S. of the 1991
Madrid Peace Conference. It is trying to boost its involvement in
the peace-making process after years of keeping a low profile.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
