<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Urges Refugees to Respect Laws </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwean government has
told all refugees in the country to respect the laws of Zimbabwe
and warned it would take stern and appropriate measures against
any transgressors.
</P>
<P>
The warning comes after some refugees forcibly occupied
offices of United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR)
in Harare, the Zimbabwe News Agency Tuesday reported.
</P>
<P>
"The government wishes to reiterate its continued commitment
in respecting its international obligations towards refugees and
other persons of concern to UNHCR," said a statement from the
Ministry of Public Service, Labor and Social Welfare.
</P>
<P>
"Whoever, the present conduct by the refugees and other
individuals compromises the government obligation to safeguard
life and property. It is also tantamount to a breach of the
obligation to respect the laws of Zimbabwe," said the statement
released Tuesday in Harare.
</P>
<P>
As for the other individuals who are not refugees or genuine
asylum-seekers, the government said the necessary, ordinary
immigration sanctions would be applied.  
</P>
