<HEADLINE> Mozambicans Urged to Contribute to State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano reiterated Tuesday that Mozambican people should try
hard to contribute to the construction of the country and the
enhancement of people's living standard.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a ceremony marking the 500 anniversary of the
first Catholic mission in Mozambique, Chissano said that
Mozambique should continue its unity and cooperation with the
Catholic on the principle that Mozambique is a non-religious
country.
</P>
<P>
Recalling Papa Joao Paulo II's visit to Mozambique in 1988,
Chissano said the visit, in days of war, had given a great
impetus to the peace and national reconciliation in the country.
