<HEADLINE> All Int'l Staff in Eastern Part of Congo Evacuated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- All international staff
in the eastern provinces of the Democratic Republic of the Congo
have been evacuated, U.N. spokesman Juan Carlos Brandt said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The last group of staff members of the United Nations and
non-governmental organizations who had been stranded in Goma as a
result of fighting in that region have been evacuated to Rwanda,
the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The fighting between the rebels and government forces in the
country flared up in recent weeks, forcing people to flee their
homes.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights and the
U.N. secretary-general have appealed to all sides to refrain from
persecution, harassment or discrimination against any segment of
the Congolese population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
