<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Urges Dialogue to Solve Kosovo Question </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan Tuesday reiterated his call for the parties to the
Kosovo conflict to immediately start dialogue to end the current
hostilities.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued through his spokesman, Annan said he
remains convinced that the only path to a solution of the Kosovo
crisis is through dialogue.
</P>
<P>
He also appealed for a concerted international effort aiming at
a peaceful solution given the evident lack of political will of
the parties within the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (FRY).
</P>
<P>
Annan reiterated his dismay at the steadily worsening situation
in Kosovo with wider implications for the region and urged the FRY
security forces to avoid acts of "scorched earth policy."
</P>
<P>
He "equally abhors the resort to violence and any suffering
which might be caused by Kosovars," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The secretary-general is concerned that the evolving crisis, if
unchecked, could lead to a large-scale humanitarian disaster, as
winter is approaching.
</P>
<P>
Noting that there are reports of a vast number of displaced
persons without food and shelter, Annan called on the
international relief organizations to intensify their efforts in
Kosovo to prevent the situation from deteriorating.
</P>
<P>
The statement was made in conjunction with the U.N. Security
Council's consultations on Annan's latest report on Kosovo which
covers the developments in July.
</P>
<P>
The situation in Kosovo is aggravated by the failure of the FRY
and the Albanian Kosovars to enter into serious negotiations on
the future status of Kosovo, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Increased heavy fighting between FRY security forces and the
so-called Kosovo Liberation Army raised the number of civilian and
military casualties to their highest point since the outbreak of
the conflict in February.
</P>
<P>
Kosovo, with an area of over 10,000 square km and a population
of 2 million, is a province of the Serbian Republic within the
FRY. Ethnic Albanians, making up 90 percent of the population,
have demanded independence of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The FRY government stands against, holding that the question
should be resolved within the incumbent Constitution, by providing
equal rights to all inhabitants in the FRY. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
