<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian President Negasso
Gidada said Tuesday that Ethiopia will not enter into
negotiations with Eritrea before the latter pulls out its forces
from Badme and the neighboring areas.
</P>
<P>
Briefing visiting German parliamentarian Uschi Eid in Addis
Ababa, President Negasso said that Ethiopia will not agree to a
cease-fire while Eritrean forces continue to occupy Ethiopian
territories.
</P>
<P>
Negasso pointed out that the Organization of African Unity
(OAU) Ambassadorial Committee has ascertained that Badme was
administered by Ethiopia before Eritrea's invasion in May.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian president said that Eritrea did not heed the
calls on it by the international community to withdraw its forces
from the areas it occupied by force.
</P>
<P>
The German parliamentarian, who is consulting with officials
of both Ethiopia and Eritrea, earlier met and held talks with the
officials in Asmara.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds died between May 6 and June 11 when a border dispute
between Ethiopia and Eritrea flared into border fightings and air
raids, the Ethiopian News Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The ministerial committee of the OAU on the dispute between
the two countries met in Ouagadougou, Burkina Faso on August 1-2,
this year.
</P>
<P>
The committee considered the report of the committee of
ambassadors which visited Eritrea and Ethiopia from June 30 to
July 9, within the framework of the mandate given to it by the
OAU high-level delegation.
</P>
<P>
The ministerial committee has submitted its recommendations to
the heads of state and members of the OAU high-level delegation
for their consideration and action. 
