Rahman Al Samawi has disclosed that the government has started
taking the executive steps for the privatization of the Aden-based
"National Bank of Yemen."
</P>
<P>
Thursday's Arab daily "Al Hayat" quoted the governor as saying
that the Ministry of Finance has appointed a financial adviser to
undertake the sale of the bank and its branches to one strategic
investor after a thorough study of its assets and activities.
</P>
<P>
The bank was founded in Aden before the declaration of unity in
1990 as public sector to back up the then Bank of Yemen. It has
branches in several southern and eastern governorates.
</P>
<P>
It is the first bank to undergo privatization in implementation
of the economic, financial and administrative reform program
undertaken by Yemen with the support of the International Monetary
Fund and the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egypt's exports increased by 12 percent in the first
quarter of this year despite the negative impact of the financial
crisis in southeast Asia, according to latest official statistics.
</P>
<P>
And the exports of cotton, onions, potatoes, rice and peanuts
rose by over 100 percent. 
