<HEADLINE> Clinton Says U.S. Vulnerable to Terrorist Attacks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 11 (Xinhua) -- President Bill Clinton said
Tuesday that the United States was more vulnerable because of its
fighting against terrorism.
</P>
<P>
"It makes us more vulnerable as targets because we have taken
the toughest stand around the world against terrorism," Clinton
said at the outset of an environmental speech at San Bruno, Calif.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, a bomb blasted at the U.S. embassy in Nairobi,
Kenya, killing more than 200 people, including 12 Americans, and
injuring over 5,000. Minutes later, the U.S. embassy in Dar es
Salaam, Tanzania, was attacked by a bomb with 10 people killed and
about 75 wounded.
