<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Introduce New Visa, Passports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Federal Government of Nigeria
is to introduce a newly-designed visa called "vignettes" to
replace the present rubber-stamp system, according to a senior
immigration official.
</P>
<P>
Alhaji Sahabi Dange, Comptroller-General of the Nigerian
Immigration Service, said Monday in Abuja, capital of Nigeria,
that orders for "vignettes" had been placed in order to enable
the service commence operations immediately.
</P>
<P>
The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) Tuesday quoted Alhaji as
saying that new passports would be introduced before the end of
the year.
</P>
<P>
The comptroller-general added that the service had mapped out
plans to ensure that applications for passports were processed
within three days. 
