<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel
arap Moi has indefinitely postponed his state visit to South
Africa in the wake of last Friday's bombing in Kenya's capital
Nairobi.
</P>
<P>
According to South African Foreign Ministry spokesman Marco
Boni, the cancellation of the visit was a combination of the bomb
blast and the fact that Kenyan Trade Minister Joseph Kamotho, who
was supposed to accompany President Moi on the trip, was injured
in the blast.
</P>
