<HEADLINE> Traffic Partly Restored on Eurasian Harbin-Manzhouli Railway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Traffic has been partly restored
on the 1,000-kilometer Harbin-Manzhouli Railway, which is part of
the first Eurasian Continental Railway. Service was suspended on
August 2 because of torrential rainfall.
</P>
<P>
Traffic resumed at 6 p.m. this evening between Manzhouli and
Zhalancun City in the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, while the
remaining 500-kilometer section between Zhalancun and Harbin,
capital of Heilongjiang Province, is still out of service.
</P>
<P>
Some 800 railway workers and armed police have been working to
restore the line, sources said.  
