<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Treatment of Pollution for Taihu Lake Emphasized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The treatment of pollution in
Taihu Lake, one of the largest lakes in east China, must be
completed within a designated period, vice governor of east
China's Zhejiang Province, Zhang Mengjin, said today.
</P>
<P>
Zhang's made these remarks at the province's fourth conference
on pollution treatment for Taihu Lake in the Yangtze River
Delta. About a third of the lake is in Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The province has spent seven years working on six water
resources projects for the treatment of pollution. Five of these
projects, one is still being designed, have been playing an
increasing role in both environmental protection and flood
control.
</P>
<P>
More funds are needed for the pollution treatment project and
project management should be strengthened, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
A plan for preventing and treating pollution in Taihu Lake has
been approved by the State Council, the nation's cabinet, which
requires that the water in Taihu Lake be clean by 2000.
</P>
<P>
Taihu Lake in the picturesque city of Hangzhou is a major
tourist attraction.  
</P>
</TEXT>
