<HEADLINE> Brolin Calls It Quits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Swedish international Tomas
Brolin announced his retirement on Wednesday at the age of 28.
</P>
<P>
After the 1994 World Cup where Sweden finished third, Brolin
broke his ankle in Sweden's a 2-0 European Championship qualifyin
g victory over Hungary on November 16, 1994.
</P>
<P>
The star midfielder missed most of the 1994-95 season because
of the ankle injury and transferred to Leeds in November 1995.
</P>
<P>
Brolin had surgery on the ankle in May of 1996 and returned to
Parma on loan for six months the following season, but never
regained form. 
</P>
