<HEADLINE> Site for Film Studio Use Awarded in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A site occupying an area of
29,800 square meters has been awarded to the Hong Kong Movie City
Company Limited at a tendered price of 78 million HK dollars (10
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
This was announced by the Information Technology and
Broadcasting Bureau and Lands Department here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to Kwong Ki-chi, secretary for Information Technology
and Broadcasting, the Hong Kong Movie City Company Limited, a
consortium with Shaw Brothers (HK) Limited as the major
shareholder, has pledged to build a state-of-the-art film studio
with advanced post-production facilities.
</P>
<P>
"This should strengthen our film production capabilities and
enhance Hong Kong's position as a post-production service center
in Asia," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We are committed to promoting the healthy and long-term
development of the film industry. We shall continue to explore
areas where the government's support is needed," he added.
</P>
<P>
The site called Tseung Kwan O Town Lot 67 in the "New
Territories" can be developed to a gross floor area of 59,600
square meters.
</P>
<P>
The initiative of making land available for film production use
is aimed at encouraging infrastructure investment in film
production and in advanced post-production technologies. 
</P>
