<HEADLINE> Nationwide Donations To Flooded Areas Mounting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A nationwide donation campaign
to aid flood-stricken areas in the Yangtze River Valley is now going
strong.
</P>
<P>
The Work Committee of the Departments Directly under the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and the Work
Committee of the State Departments under the CPC Central Committee
issued a joint circular recently, asking all personnel to make
donations to the flood victims.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Civil Affairs issued an emergency notice
calling on localities to effectively organize the campaign, and
make sure that all donated funds and relief materials be used
properly for the flood victims only.
</P>
<P>
The donation activities must be brought under the supervision
of auditing departments, the media and the public, the notice
stressed.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan, one of the hardest-hit cities, has so far received more
than 20 million yuan in cash and materials, and the city
government has set up a working group to follow the entire process
of distributing and using the donations.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, China's largest economic and financial center,
donated 15 million yuan to Hubei Province this afternoon, and
private entrepreneur Guo Ziwen from south China's Guangdong
Province also donated 500,000 yuan to the province.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region in northwest China, which is
relatively impoverished, collected four million yuan worth of
relief supplies and had them flown to the flooded areas along the
Yangtze River tonight.  
</P>
</TEXT>
