<HEADLINE> Scores Injured in Finnish Train Collision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Scores of people were injured
when a Finnish intercity passenger train and a freight train
collided head-on early on Wednesday, a Finnish News Agency report
said.
</P>
<P>
The intercity train with 50 passengers was leaving Suonenjoki
station for Helsinki when it was involved in a head-on, low-speed
collision with a freight train travelling the other way. The line
had to be closed.
</P>
<P>
About 30,000 kiloliters of a chemical material carried by the
freight train leaked out.
</P>
<P>
Investigators were studying the site, but the cause of the
accident was still unknown.
</P>
<P>
Finland was shaken in May by its second-worst postwar train
disaster when a passenger train derailed, killing 11 people and
injuring more than 30. 
</P>
