<HEADLINE> New Law Ensures Investment Rights of Overseas Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A new local regulation aimed at
protecting the investment rights of overseas Chinese has recently
been approved by the Standing Committee of the provincial People's
Congress of east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
"The regulation will help improve Fujian's investment
environment and stop such illicit activities as arbitrary charges
levied on overseas Chinese investors," said a senior provincial
official.
</P>
<P>
The province has benefited greatly from its large population of
overseas Chinese who contribute some 70 percent of the province's
overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The regulation clearly states that the necessary examinations
of enterprises funded by overseas Chinese can only be conducted
by a certain group of government departments, and also must be in
strict accordance with the law.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the regulation legalizes preferential treatment for
overseas Chinese investors in areas such as taxation and
infrastructure.  
</P>
</TEXT>
