<HEADLINE> URGENT: Lesotho Soldiers Fire at Protesters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Lesotho army fired stun
grenades at protesters outside King Letsie III's palace in Maseru
Wednesday afternoon, South African Press Association (SAPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
SAPA quoted opposition parties spokeswoman Monica Mopeli as saying
there was chaos and panic when soldiers fired stun grenades.
</P>
<P>
"They started shooting at 2.10 p.m. (1210 GMT) and it is chaos here
with people running in all directions. We have not established how
many, if any, people have been injured at this stage," she said.
</P>
<P>
The army action followed an earlier order by army chief
Lieutenant-Colonel Makhula Motakeng for the protesters to disperse.
</P>
<P>
The order was ignored. 
</P>
