<HEADLINE> HK's Outstanding Retail Companies Praised </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Giordano International
Ltd. has been named the Service Industry Leader by the Hong Kong
Retail Management Association (HKRMA) for the fourth period of the
Mystery Shoppers Program conducted by the HKRMA during January -
June 1998.
</P>
<P>
It was also named the Service Category Leader in the category
of Fashion and Accessories, the HKRMA announced at a press
conference held on Wednesday at the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
The other service category leaders are the Sa Sa International
Holdings Ltd. in the category of Beauty Products and Cosmetics;
the Duty Free Shoppers Hong Kong Ltd. in the category of
Department Stores; the SmarTone Mobile Communications Ltd. in the
category of Electronic &AMP; Electrical Appliances.
</P>
<P>
The service category leaders in the categories of Food,
Furniture &AMP; Home Accessories, Specialty Stores and Supermarkets
and Convenience Stores went respectively to the Domino's Pizza -
Connor Pizza Ltd., the Eurodecor Furniture (Holdings) Ltd., the
Shanghai Tang and Oliver's Delicatessen.
</P>
<P>
At the conference, a Certificate of Achievement was presented
to each company by the HKRMA Chairman Philip Ma.
</P>
<P>
The industry-wide Mystery Shoppers Program is organized by the
HKRMA on an ongoing bi-annual basis.
</P>
<P>
The objectives of the program are to improve the overall
standard of customer service in the retail industry and in
recognizing outstanding retail companies for being quality service
providers.
</P>
<P>
A total of 80 retail companies representing 2,072 retail
outlets have participated in the program for the period of January
to June 1998.
</P>
<P>
Participating companies were grouped into eight retail business
categories. Through a team of well-trained mystery shoppers,
mystery visits were conducted among participating companies and
their performance were carefully checked and monitored according
to the assessment guidelines laid out.
</P>
<P>
Companies being visited were assessed on nine key customer
service related assessment criteria which include staff
appearance, store housekeeping, greeting and approaching
customers, staff attitude, product knowledge, answering customers
objections, till service, customers leaving and team spirit.
</P>
<P>
The program was officially launched in 1996 and the next period
of the HKRMA Mystery Shoppers Program is being held from July to
December 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
