<HEADLINE> Management Modernization Key to Development of Western China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Management modernization is the
key to the economic development of western China. This is the
consensus reached recently by experts and scholars from both sides
of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
During the 6th Cross-Straits Seminar on Chinese Modernization,
which ended Tuesday in the city of Lanzhou, capital of northwest
China's Gansu Province, participants all agreeed that despite
natural environmental factors, an underdeveloped management method
is the primary cause of the backwardness in vast western China.
</P>
<P>
In order to realize the modernization of management, local
governments must improve the efficiency of government
departments, enhance the exploitation and training of talented
people, and establish a modern enterprise system in western China,
according to the conferees
</P>
<P>
They also believe that local governments should do their utmost
to improve infrastructure construction, adhere to the reform and
opening-up policy, and rejuvenate western China through science
and technology.  
</P>
</TEXT>
