<HEADLINE> Fifth Flood Peak Forms on Yangtze </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The fifth Yangtze River flood
crest, which has formed due to heavy rains in the Three Gorges
area, once again raised water levels on the upper reaches of
the river.
</P>
<P>
The water level at Shashi in Hubei Province hit 44.66 meters by
noon today, up 0.1 of a meter on the Tuesday level. Other reports
issued by the State Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters
indicate that the water level at Hankou rose 0.08 of a meter to
29.18 meters, while the level at Jiujiang, Jiangxi Province,
dropped 0.05 of a meter to 22.74 meters.
</P>
<P>
Water levels in the Shishou-Luoshan and Wuxue-Jiujiang sections
continue to hover at record highs.
</P>
<P>
The latest reports indicate that water levels along the
Nenjiang and Songhua rivers in northeast China hit 149.18 meters
at Qiqihar and 118.94 meters at Harbin, and the water levels are
continuing to rise in both areas. 
</P>
