<HEADLINE> Relief Supplies Reach Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The first shipment of flood
relief supplies sent by the State Flood Control and Drought Relief
Headquarters arrived in flood ravaged areas in Inner Mongolia
early this morning.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rainfall in the eastern section of the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region in north China between August 8-12. Resulting
flood water caused a breach in the levee at Dorbenxin, Jalaid
Banner (county) in the Xinggan League (prefecture) on Tuesday. The
dam at the Uradgai Reservoir on the Xinlin Gol Grasslands
collapsed early this morning.
</P>
<P>
The state flood control headquarters immediately shipped two
million plastic bags, 30 lifeboats and rafts, as well as 5,000
life preservers from Hebei and Jiangsu provinces. Local
authorities are currently distributing relief materials to
affected areas.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Water Resources has also allocated relief funds
of over four million yuan to Inner Mongolia and the Ministry of
Civil Affairs has earmarked an equal amount of funding for the
region.
</P>
<P>
The Air Force Branch of the People's Liberation Army and armed
police units have sent dozens of helicopters and soldiers to
affected areas and more than 100 medical teams have rushed to the
scene.
</P>
<P>
No casualties or outbreaks of epidemic diseases have been
reported.  
</P>
</TEXT>
