<HEADLINE> Sichuan Sustains Heavy Losses From Flooding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Flooding has caused losses of
more than four billion yuan in southwest China's Sichuan Province,
according to provincial official sources.
</P>
<P>
Rainstorms and flooding since May have claimed the life of 314
people, left 1,325 people injured and inundated 158 counties with
a total population of 19.35 million people.
</P>
<P>
Meteorologists predict the rain will continue through early
October.
</P>
<P>
While addressing an emergency meeting, Vice-Governor Jing
Zhengshu called on government officials to supervise operations
along levees, closely monitor weather forecasts, arrange for
emergency shipments of flood relief materials, ensure the
well-being of local residents and organize epidemic prevention
efforts.  
