<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Author Charged in Court for alleged Defaming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Khalid Jafri, author of the
book "50 Dalil Mengapa Anwar Tidak Boleh Jadi PM" ("50 reasons why
Anwar can not become PM" was charged in the Sessions Court here
Wednesday with maliciously publishing false news.
</P>
<P>
The book is alleged to defame Deputy Prime Minister Anwar
Ibrahim.
</P>
<P>
Khalid, 58, pleaded not guilty to publishing the book which
contained "false news" in para 12 of page 29, at the office of
Media Pulau Lagenda here in May this year.
</P>
<P>
The charge under Section 8A (1) of the Printing Presses and
Publications Act 1984 carries a jail term not exceeding three
years or fine not exceeding 20,000 ringgit (about 5,000 U.S.
dollars), or both on conviction.
</P>
<P>
Judge Mohamad K. Abdul Rahman fixed August 19 for mention of
the case. The court room was packed during the proceedings.
</P>
<P>
The Judge granted Khalid bail of 5,000 ringgit (about 1,250
U.S. dollars) in one surety as applied by defense counsel Mohamed
Haniff Khatri Abdullah who said that there was no danger posed as
an injunction had been obtained against the author Khalid and
Media Pulau Lagenda.
</P>
<P>
Mohamed Haniff told reporters later that he filed an appeal on
Monday against the decision of the High Court on July 31 granting
the injunction to Anwar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
