<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed higher Wednesday on a technical
rebound.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index rose 7.49
points to 342.19, the all-share Emas Index added 1.13 points to
87.68, the Industrial Index was 5.85 points higher at 705.57 while
the Second Board Index dropped 0.09 of a point to 79.12.
</P>
<P>
Gainers led losers 334 by 246 while 152 counters were unchanged
and 192 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover was 123.333 million shares worth 199.062
million ringgit (about 47.508 million U.S. dollars) against
Tuesday's 117.349 million shares valued at 186.707 million
ringgit (about 44.56 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board volume rose to 119.617 million shares worth
194.553 million ringgit (about 46.432 million U.S. dollars) from
113.282 million shares valued at 182.168 million ringgit (about
43.476 million U.S. dollars) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover fell to 3.716 million shares worth
4.509 million ringgit (about 1.076 million U.S. dollars) from
Tuesday's 4.067 million shares valued at 4.538 million ringgit
(about 1.083 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off market deals fell to 1.471 million shares worth 4.320
million ringgit (about 1.031 million U.S. dollars) from 2.526
million shares valued at 5.621 million ringgit (about 1.341
million U.S. dollars) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 8.373
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
11.945 million shares, construction 7.843 million shares,
trading/services 40.671 million shares, infrastructure 836,000
shares, finance 25.508 million shares, hotels 401,000 shares,
properties 11.180 million shares, plantation 4.751 million shares,
mining 546,000 shares, trusts 127,000 shares, closed/fund 33,000
shares and loans 7.401 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
