<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Host SAARC Speakers' Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The SAARC Speakers' Conference
will be held here in December this year to discuss ways of
attaining higher excellence by the legislatures of the member
countries.
</P>
<P>
The decision was taken at the first day's session of a
three-day meeting of Secretaries General of SAARC (South Asian
Association for Regional Cooperation) Parliaments that began here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
An exact date of the conference, tentatively in the last week
of December, will be decided at the concluding session of the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, presided over by Bangladesh Parliament Secretary
Quazi M. Manzur-I-Mowla and attended by representatives from all
SAARC member states, also chalked out details of the program of
the SAARC Speakers Conference, such as presentation of keynote
speeches and publication of booklet containing country profiles.
</P>
<P>
The SAARC, established here in 1985, groups Bangladesh, Bhutan,
India, the Maldives, Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka. 
</P>
</TEXT>
