<HEADLINE> Malaysia Assures U.S. Embassy Staff of Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Police are
beefing up security at the U.S. embassy here to assure the embassy
staff of safety following last week's bomb attacks on U.S.
embassies in Kenya and Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Deputy Home Minister Tajol Rosli Ghazali Wednesday
assured the staff of the United States embassy here of their
safety as the embassy was being put on heavy guard.
</P>
<P>
"I think the U.S. embassy in Malaysia will be safe but we are
taking the necessary precautions. We would like to assure the U.S.
embassy staff that to us the embassy in our country will be safe,
but we are giving extra police security just to make sure. We are
confident that they will be safe," he told reporters here.
</P>
<P>
Police are providing additional security to the embassy which
too has its own security.
</P>
<P>
Tajol Rosli said providing the additional security was not
because the authorities thought that something would happen to the
embassy but because Malaysia always liked to take precaution.
</P>
</TEXT>
