<HEADLINE> Plane Crashes in E. Angola, Killing Pilot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A Russian-made Antonov-12 cargo
plane crashed in eastern Angola, killing its Russian pilot and
injuring seven passengers, the Portuguese News Agency Lusa
reported in Lisbon Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Lusa, in a report from Luanda, said the pilot lost control of
the plane which veered off the runway on landing at Saurimo
airport in Lunda Sul province on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Most of the injured were in critical condition, Lusa quoted
a doctor as saying.
</P>
<P>
The plane belonged to an unidentified private Angolan company,
the agency said. It gave no details on the identities of the
passengers or what cargo the aircraft was carrying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
