<HEADLINE> 14 Die in Nigerian Road Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 12 (Xinhua) -- At least 14 people, including one
soldier, were feared dead and seven others seriously wounded
Tuesday when an army truck collided with a passenger bus on a
highway in Kwara State, western Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The police had to spend several hours trying to rescue
passengers, the Daily Times reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The national newspaper quoted witnesses as reporting that the
accident occurred around 21:30 p.m. (local time) as the army
truck, loaded with soldiers on its way to Lagos, collided with
the bus bound for the capital Abuja. 
