<HEADLINE> Iranians Clash with Pakistani Embassy Staff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Violent clashes broke out
Wednesday morning between Iranian demonstrators demanding the
release of their diplomats by the Afghan Taliban and staff members
of the Pakistani embassy here.
</P>
<P>
Violence occurred when the demontrators tried to break into the
embassy.
</P>
<P>
A reporter from the official news agency IRNA, Ablfazl Shaker,
tried to force his way into the embassy and ask Pakistani
diplomats to answer questions about Islamabad's support for the
Taliban militia.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani embassy staff dragged Shaker into the embassy when he
pushed open the main gate. The gate was shut immediately and
Shaker scuffled with the embassy staff while more demonstrators
tried to get into.
</P>
<P>
The glass of the gate was broken, and some Iranian
demonstrators accused that it was broken intentionally by
Pakistani embassy staff in order to worsen the situation.
</P>
<P>
In front of the main gate were about 100 people, mainly IRNA
staff members and relatives of the IRNA reporter Mahmoud Saremi
and 32 Iranian drivers, claimed to be captured by the Taliban in
northern Afghanistan Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In addition, 11 Iranian diplomats were also reportedly taken
captive by the Taliban forces who took over Mazar-e-Sharif, the
main stronghold of the opposition Northern Alliance. more



12/08/98 8:44 GMT

