<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swedish Stocks Down 3.09 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Swedish stock prices plummeted
3.09 percent on Tuesday, following a worldwide trend.
</P>
<P>
In Sweden, service companies were the hardest hit, down by an
average of 4.17 percent. Banking and financial companies were also
affected, with a plunge of 4.15 percent.
</P>
<P>
In neighboring Finland, Helsinki stocks exchange finished the
day down by a dramatic 5.50 percent. Oslo slid by 3.50 percent,
while Copenhagen lost 3.77 percent.
</P>
<P>
Asian currency worries, the bleak mood on Wall Street and a 9
percent plunge in Russian shares were some of the negative factors
moving through European markets.
</P>
<P>
Driven by sell-offs by foreign investors, the downward slide
in Sweden may continue for some time, analysts said. But brokers
predicted that long-term prospects remain solid.
</P>
<P>
"We see the recent price adjustments as healthy and necessary,"
said Swedish Foreningssparbanken analyst Rodney Alven. He said
shares of banking and financial companies and manufacturing firms
look attractive at current low levels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
