<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Ranks 7th in Printing Ink Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- China has emerged as the world's
seventh largest producer of printing ink, with an annual output of
74,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attribute the growth in production to the nation's
booming printing sector.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey conducted by the State Bureau of Quality
and Technology Supervision revealed that major producers have
maintained stable quality, with a noticeable fall in quality
levels for smaller firms.
</P>
<P>
The survey indicated that the number of printing ink products
meeting quality standards grew by 2.9 percentage points when
compared to 1992.
</P>
<P>
The survey also revealed that all counterfeit printing ink
products failed to meet quality standards.
</P>
<P>
China has over 400 printing ink producers. The survey
showed that 80 percent of the 225 products manufactured by 35
enterprises reached quality standards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
