<HEADLINE> 4 Wounded in Cellphone Bomb Blast in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- An improvised bomb inserted in a
cellular phone exploded Wednesday inside a shopping center in a
northern Manila suburb, wounding four people, police said.
</P>
<P>
Police said that the blast took place in Caloocan City and one
of the four wounded was in critical conditions.
</P>
<P>
The bomb went off when a construction plumber was having the
cellular phone, which he accidentally found earlier, fixed by a
technician.
</P>
<P>
The cellular phone stall's manager lost his left hand when the
bomb's fuse ignited as he reloaded its battery. Three others, who
were hit by sharpnels, were rushed to a nearby hospital.
</P>
<P>
Police said the culprit responsible in placing the explosive
device in the cellphone's battery pack could be a bomb expert.
</P>
