<HEADLINE> Earthquake Hits Central Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake measuring 4.6
on the Richter scale jolted Nagano Prefecture in central Japan
Wednesday afternoon, the Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no reports of casualties or damage, and no tsunami
or tidal wave warnings were issued
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred at at 3:13 p.m. (local time), was the
latest in a series of earthquakes to hit the region since last
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Tuesday, a quake measuring 4.1 on the Richter scale hit
the region, followed by three minor quakes, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred at 9:40 a.m., was centered at about
10 kilometers underground in central Nagano Prefecture, the agency
said. 
</P>
