<HEADLINE> Philippines to Build Large-scale Power Plant in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government
approved Tuesday a 1.9-billion-U.S.-dollar coal-fired power plant
project to increase power supply in the southern island of
Mindanao beginning 1999.
</P>
<P>
The project was approved by the governing board of the National
Economic and Development Authority (NEDA), chaired by President
Joseph Estrada.
</P>
<P>
The coal-fired power plant, with a capacity of 200 megawatt,
will be constructed in Misamis Oriental province in northern
Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
The power project is estimated to cost 1.9 billion dollars, of
which 388.5 million will be the government's foreign exchange
component. The rest will come from the local counterpart fund.
</P>
<P>
The plant will be constructed under the
build-operate-and-transfer (BOT) scheme. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
