</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Kosovo ethnic Albanian militants Tuesday continued
to attack Serbian police posts along the highway between Decani
and Djakovica, killing five policemen and injuring six others in
three days.
</P>
<P>
But the rebels were driven back to the mountainous area of
Junik, the Tanjug news agency said. The attacks were designed to
help hundreds of armed ethnic Albanians to break out of the siege
in Junik by Yugoslav troops. (Yugoslavia-Kosovo-Attacks) 
</P>
