<HEADLINE> China Hosts 30 Million Foreign Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A total of 30.18 million foreign
tourists visited China during the first six months of this year in
spite of the Asian financial crisis, up 13 percent on the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the China National Tourism
Administration (CNTA) show that Chine earned 5.96 billion US
dollars from international tourism during the period, up 8.81
percent.
</P>
<P>
The Asian financial crisis lowered the consumption capacity of
people in related countries and resulted in an 8.11 percent
decline in the number of Asian tourists visiting China during the
first six months. The growing number of tourists from other
continents, however, has offset adverse influences, according to
CNTA officials.
</P>
<P>
In terms of the 15 major tourist markets, the number of
visitors from both Australia and Kazakhstan grew by over 20
percent, with a significant decline in the number of tourists from
Thailand, Malaysia and the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
The number of tourists from Thailand fell by a hefty 34.16
percent, with slight drops in the number of arrivals from Japan
and the Philippines and various levels of growth in visitors from
other countries.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the number of Hong Kong and Macao compatriots
visiting inland areas grew by 16.19 percent, with the figure for
overseas Chinese growing by 21.53 percent. Tourism revenues for
tourists from the respective groups grew by 44.28 percent and 9.25
percent.
</P>
<P>
The number of Russian tourists fell by 5.72 percent in June,
with the first drop in over two years blamed on financial turmoil
in Russia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
