<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban Capture Another Key Northern Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban militia on
Wednesday were reported to have captured a key northern town of
Pul-i-Khumri in their latest fighting against the opposition
Northern Alliance.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here Wednesday afternoon from the Afghan
capital of Kabul said that Pul-i-Khumri fell into the Taliban
forces around 10:30 a.m. local time following a heavy overnight
attack.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Taliban spokesman Abdul Hai Mutmaen as saying
that "our forces launched massive attacks last night and this
morning and captured these areas from the enemy (the Northern
Alliance)."
</P>
<P>
The Taliban militia continued their victorious march in
northern Afghanistan Tuesday when they captured Taloqan, capital
of Takhar province and a stronghold of former president
Burhanuddin Rabbani and his defense minister Ahmad Shah Masood.
</P>
</TEXT>
