<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing-Guangzhou Railway Line Doing Well despite Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing-Guangzhou Railway
Line, a trunk north-south line, has remained open during the
recent serious flooding on the Yangtze River thanks to help from
the People's Liberation Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
The line has helped move a large amount of flood relief
materials and reinforcements to flood-hit areas in Hubei and Hunan
provinces. The eastern side of Dongting Lake in Hunan has been a
vital facility for protecting the line.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji made a special trip to the dike during the
flooding to urge PLA personnel and civilians to make every effort
to protect dikes and the line.
</P>
<P>
For more than 40 days, 7,000 soldiers have been working to
protect the dike and have stopped problems in more than 100
places, shipping 200,000 bags of sand, fortifying 4 km of dikes,
and building walls, diversion ditches, and cofferdams.
</P>
<P>
A fourth flood crest on the Yangtze passed Dongting yesterday
and a fifth is expected to start tomorrow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
