<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Sells out 17 State-Owned Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian privatization
agency said it has secured an income of over 717.5 million Birr
(102.5 million U.S. Dollars) from the sale to investors of 17
state-owned enterprises under its administration.
</P>
<P>
A report from the Ethiopian Herald Wednesday quoted Beshah
Azemte, general manager of the agency as saying that the
enterprises sold include business premises, hotel,
agro-industries, factories and agricultural development projects
located in different parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Beshah added that the organizations were sold by auction in
which local and foreign investors attended.
</P>
<P>
The general manager noted that the agency has received a total
of 2,960 in second round petitions submitted by claimants of the
previously nationalized enterprises and has already begun
consideration of 387 of them. 
</P>
