<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stage ii of Japan-Lanka Friendship Bridge Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Construction work on Stage ii of
the Japan-Sri Lanka Friendship Bridge was inaugurated by Sri
Lankan Transport and Highways Minister A.H.M. Fowzie Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It replaces the former Victoria Bridge constructed in 1895 at
Peliyagoda, the gateway to Colombo city from the North.
</P>
<P>
The ministry expects to complete the bridge at a cost of 26.1
million U.S. dollars, of which 22.2 million dollars will be
provided by the Overseas Economic Cooperation Fund of Japan. The
balance funds will come from the Sri Lankan government, according
to official sources.
</P>
<P>
The tender for the construction work has been awarded to
Khajima Corporation of Japan and the Keang Nam company of South
Korea.
</P>
<P>
The construction work is due to be completed by the end of the
year 2000 and will be opened to traffic the following year.
</P>
<P>
The first stage of the bridge was completed in 1990's at a cost
of about 13 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
After completion, the bridge will be 228 meters long, 26 meters
wide and will facilitate four lanes of traffic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
