<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Hydropower Station On China's Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Work began on the 13th
hydro-electric power station on the upper reaches of China's
Yellow River in Qinghai Province over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The Nina station is on the main stream of the Yellow River in
Guide County and is the third power station on the upper reaches
of the river on the Longyang Gorge-Qingtong Gorge section.
</P>
<P>
It will have a 160,000-kw capacity and a designed generating
capacity of 736 million kw/hours of electricity a year. Its
estimated cost is 1.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Nina Hydro-electric Power Co. Ltd. is responsible for fund
raising and the Huanghe (Yellow River) Power Development Co. Ltd
has a controlling interest. Huanghe Power is owned by three firms,
one of them from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The first generator will start generating power in 2000 and the
entire station will be finished at the end of 2001.  
</P>
</TEXT>
