<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Grain Borer Threatens 80 Percent of Yield in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A highly-destructive pest is
threatening to wipe out as much as 80 percent of harvested grain
in Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The larger grain borer has struck all parts of Zambia and the
pest is spreading fast.
</P>
<P>
A warning against the bug has been issued by Zambia's National
Pest Containment and Control Program. It is appealing to farmers
to take urgent measures to control the bug by using pesticide,
The Post reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The larger grain borer was not known in Zambia until 1995 when
its presence is recorded in the Northern Province, which borders
Tanzania, said the paper.
</P>
<P>
Since then, the destructive bug has moved to other provinces
in Zambia through imported maize from Tanzania to offset a
shortfall brought about by drought three years ago.
</P>
<P>
The seeds were distributed across Zambia by non-governmental
organizations as relief food. 
</P>
</TEXT>
