<HEADLINE> China's Leading Passenger Car Venture Increases Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Both production and sales of
China's largest joint-venture passenger car manufacturer were up
in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Yaxing-Benz, a joint venture of the Jiangsu Yaxing Passenger
Car Group and Germany's Mercedes Benz, produced 2,014 passenger
cars and sold 1,924 in the first half of this year, up 61.6
percent and 59.5 percent respectively from the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
The venture did 298 million yuan in business in the first six
months, and sold more than 100 chassis between January and June.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture was built at a cost of 100 million U.S.
dollars and began operation at the end of last year. It has a
designed production capacity of 7,000 large passenger cars and
12,000 chassis per year.  
</P>
