<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rural Guangdong Enterprises Report Robust Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Village and township
enterprises in south China's Guangdong Province witnessed robust
development in the first half of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show that the industrial output value for
related firms totaled 328.5 billion yuan during the period, a
year-on-year rise of 11.86 percent, with pretax profits rising by
8.47 percent to 15.69 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Private firms also enjoyed impressive progress and outstripped
the performance of collective enterprises during the first six
months, with the sector's total output value growing by 15.17
percent, value-added by 12.52 percent and business turnover by
15.49 percent.
</P>
<P>
Pan Jiayu, director of the Guangdong Rural Enterprise Bureau,
attributed the private sector's performance to preferential
policies introduced by the local government.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also show that rural enterprises enjoyed a 12.2
percent rise in exports to end the period at 72.53 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The notable achievement has been attributed to increased
exports to the UNITED STATES, Europe and Africa at a time when the
traditional markets in southeast Asia remain sluggish due to the
ongoing financial crisis, according to Pan.
</P>
<P>
The figures also revealed dampened efficiency with the
production-sales ratio dropping by two percentage points to 90.54
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980812.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Northern Chinese Reservoir's Spillway Collapses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Because of torrential rains, the
spillway on the Uradgai Reservoir in north China's Inner Mongolia
caved in early this morning.
</P>
<P>
In less than two hours, the spillway widened from 40 m. to 200
m. and water flow increased five-fold. The communications link
between the reservoir and the regional flood control headquarters
was also cut.
</P>
<P>
No casualties have been reported so far.
</P>
<P>
The reservoir, which is located in the East Ujumqin Banner
(county) on the Xin Gol League Grassland, is a major state
reservoir with a storage capacity of 280 million cu.m. The local
government has organized an emergency repair team and an effort is
being made to restore communications. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
