<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Records GDP Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province,
one of the nation's economic powerhouses, posted a gross domestic
product of 316.3 billion yuan in the first half of this year, a
year-on-year rise of eight percent.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show the period growth rate was three
percentage points below the official 11 percent target for 1998.
</P>
<P>
Severe natural disasters contributed to the five percent fall
in Jiangsu's agricultural output value during the first six months
compared with the same period last year. The industrial output
value grew by 8.9 percent, with the figure for the service sector
up by 11.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu invested 47.9 billion yuan in fixed assets during the
first half of this year, up 17.8 percent on the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
The province's retail sales for consumer goods totaled 108
billion yuan, up four percent.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu has countered the effects of the Asian financial crisis
by expanding efforts to tap export markets in Europe, the
United States, Africa and the Middle East. The province's foreign
trade volume surged 18.2 percent to reach 12.3 billion US dollars
for the January-June period, with exports rising 12.9 percent to
8.1 billion US dollars.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
