<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liberty Edges Mercury 79-78 in Overtime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The New York Liberty nipped
the Phoenix Mercury 79-78 in overtime to improve its playoff
chances in the WNBA competition in New York on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
Sophia Witherspoon scored 17 points for the winning team,
which are tied with Cleveland for the second place in the Eastern
Conference with 16 wins and 10 losses, just one-half game behind
Charlotte (17-10). New York and Phoenix entered the game tied
for the fourth and final WNBA playoff spot.
</P>
<P>
Phoenix's Kristi Harrower missed a potential game-winning
3-point at the buzzer to seal the Liberty's win. Witherspoon's
layup gave New York a 74-73 lead with 1:15 left in overtime. She
grabbed the missed shot and was fouled by Umeki Webb before
making the second of her free throws to make it 75-73.
</P>
<P>
New York shot 50 percent (28-for-56), while Phoenix shot 46
percent (29-for-63). Jennifer Gillom pulled Phoenix within one
point with 8.1 seconds remaining. She led Phoenix with 21
points, Bridget Pettis added 16.
</P>
<P>
Rebecca Lobo had 13 points and 11 rebounds, while Vickie
Johnson netted 11 points for the Liberty.
</P>
<P>
In another game tonight, the Detroit Shock beat the Sacramento
Monarchs 50-41. 
</P>
</TEXT>
