<HEADLINE> Holyfield to Defend Title against Bean Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Evander Holyfield, who has
not fought since Novement, will defend his International Boxing
Federation (IBF) title on September 19 against top contender
Vaughn Bean at the Georgia Dome in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
Holyfield also holds the World Boxing Association title but
will not put it on the line against lightly regarded Bean.
</P>
<P>
Holyfield was slated for a title defense against Henry
Akinwande in June but saw the challenger withdraw when pre-fight
testing revealed he had hepatitis.
</P>
<P>
At a news conference this afternoon in Atlanta, Holyfield
admitted that he will share a portion of the expenses to stage
the fight in his hometown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
