<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kosovo Militants Attack Army Posts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Kosovo ethnic Albanian
militants Tuesday continued to attack Serbian police posts along
the highway between Decani and Djakovica, killing five policemen
and injuring six others in three days.
</P>
<P>
But the rebels were driven back to the mountainous area of
Junik, the Tanjug news agency said.
</P>
<P>
The attacks were designed to help hundreds of armed ethnic
Albanians to break out of the siege in Junik by Yugoslav troops.
</P>
<P>
The ethnic Albanian militants were routed by Yugoslav security
forces in Orahovac and Malissevo two weeks ago and fled to Junik
near the border area in an attempt to cross into Albania.
</P>
<P>
The Serbian Interior Ministry was reported to have discovered
in Malissevo files about Kosovo Liberation Army men including
their pictures and videotapes, the news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Ministry officials said that it would track down the armed
militants and other accomplices according to the files they have
intercepted.
</P>
<P>
In Kosovo, 52 policemen have been killed since January 1,
according to a Serbian toll. Since the conflict erupted at the end
of February more than 500 people have been killed in Kosovo, most
of them ethnic Albanians who account for 90 percent of the local
population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
