<HEADLINE> Munz, Thompson Win in U.S. Swimming Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Diana Munz and Chris
Thompson beat their strong rivals to win their races on the
opening day of the U.S. Swimming National Championships in
Clovis, California on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Munz, silver medalist in the 1998 world championships, won the
women's 800-meter freestyle over Olympic and world champion
Brooke Bennett in eight minutes 31.74 seconds to Bennett's
8:35.74.
</P>
<P>
"I know she can go faster, so it will be a race in our events
the rest of the meet," said Munz. "It means a lot to me. She's a
great swimmer and I'am amazed."
</P>
<P>
Thompson won the men's 800-meter freestyle title with a
7:58.26, which makes him the 15th-fastest man ever in the event
and the sixth-fastest American ever.
</P>
<P>
Thompson trailed Tom Dolanfor the first 300 meters, but roared
to front to win the race. Only two finals featured today.
</P>
</TEXT>
