<HEADLINE> Three More U.S. Embassies Suspend Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 12 (Xinhua) -- U.S. embassies in Egypt,
Malaysia and Yemen have suspended operations amid increased
threats of terrorism.
</P>
<P>
An unidentified U.S. official was quoted by the Associated
Press (AP) as saying that the warnings were based on "credible
information."
</P>
<P>
Assistant Secretary of State Patrick Kennedy said that about
half a dozen U.S. embassies had suspended operations after the
attacks in Kenya and Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Embassy in Swaziland received threat call and sniffer
dogs searched the embassy and a nearby building housing embassy
offices and found nothing, the AP said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Embassy in Kampala, Uganda, remained closed for a
second day Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
