<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand to Facilitate Furniture Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Thailand is to set up a working
group to help boost the country's shrinking furniture export, a
government press release available Wednesday said.
</P>
<P>
The working group will revise and improve the rules,
regulations and measures which have been impediments to furniture
export.
</P>
<P>
The press release quoted the Commerce Ministry as saying that
the rules and regulations concerned, the measures regulated by
government agencies, the financial liquidity, information and
public relations have been major obstacles of Thai furniture
export.
</P>
<P>
According to the press release, Thai furniture export has been
decreased continuously from 1995 to 1998.
</P>
<P>
The value of Thai furniture export was 755.3 million U.S.
dollars in 1995, while in 1997 the value dropped to 725.7 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the first six months of 1998, the total export was only
288.3 million dollars, down 20.9 percent from the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
The decrease in Thai furniture export can partly be attributed
to the sluggishness of the Japanese market, which has been reduced
by 37.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The other two major markets for Thai furniture export are the
United States and the European Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
