BANGKOK, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's Economic Ministers'
Council Meeting has approved a proposal of the Electricity
Generating Authority of Thailand (EGAT) to issue 300 million U.S.
dollar bonds in the international market, a government press
release available Wednesday said.
</P>
<P>
According to the press release, the World Bank will be the
bonds guarantor and an agreement with the World Bank will be
signed by Savit Bhotivihok, Minister to the Prime Minister's
Office, joined by heads of agencies concerned, namely the National
Economic and Social Development Board, the Finance Ministry, EGAT,
and the National Energy Policy Office.
</P>
<P>
However, the press release has not given the specific date of
the signing.
</P>
<P>
The EGAT's bonds issuance will help seek the financial sources
at a low cost for the construction of the power plants as earlier
approved by the Cabinet.
</P>
<P>
However, in order to sustain the stability of financial status
of the EGAT as required by the World Bank's conditions, the
government has to consider increasing electricity price,
decreasing the amount of revenue which has to be forwarded to the
state, downsizing the EGAT's investment plan, increasing the
efficiency, or privatization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
