<HEADLINE> Cambodia Appeals For Aid to Fight Dengue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Red Cross President
Bun Rany appealed Tuesday for help in fighting the dengue fever
epidemic sweeping Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
In a speech broadcast on Bayon Radio, the second prime
minister's wife announced plans to train hundreds of community
health educators to help prevent the spread of the disease.
</P>
<P>
"Cambodian Red Cross wishes to appeal to all Cambodian people,
businessmen and international organizations to contribute towards the
budget for this project," Bun Rany said.
</P>
<P>
The dengue epidemic sweeping Cambodia escalated recently. A
total 6,500 child cases have been reported this year, with 144
dead, according to statistics from the World Health Organization.
</P>
<P>
Dengue fever generally peaks during the rainy season because of
the enhanced breeding conditions provided by dampness. But an
unseasonably warm December gave rise to an early outbreak, the
results of which are now being seen in the scale of the wet-season
epidemic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
