<HEADLINE> Bahamas Returns 65 Illegal Immigrants to Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The Bahamas government returned
65 illegal Cuban immigrants Tuesday who had tried to enter the
United States via this Caribbean nation during May and June, Radio
Reloja reported.
</P>
<P>
Among the illegal immigrants, 45 were men, 11 women and nine
children. They were from Havana and other Cuban provinces.
</P>
<P>
In the past seven months, the Bahamas has returned a total of
329 illegal immigrants to Cuba.
</P>
<P>
The Bahamas government reiterated that it will stick to the
migration agreement it signed with Cuba in January 1996.
</P>
<P>
Cuba has emphasized that migration from its national territory
has to be done via legal and orderly ways. 
