<HEADLINE> Hungarian Foreign Trade Increases in First Half year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Hungary's exports amounted to
10.8 billion U.S. dollars in the first half of the year, up 23.4
percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Its imports reached 12.1 billion dollars in the first half of
the year, up 20.9 percent, the Hungarian Telegraph Agency quoted
official statistics as saying Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Machine exports and imports contributed to the substantial
growth.
</P>
<P>
Official sources of the Hungarian Economic Ministry predicted
that the country's foreign trade would register an 18 to 20
percent increase this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
