<HEADLINE> Central America, Dominican Republic Negotiate Free Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Foreign trade officials from
Central America and the Dominican Republic will meet in Guatemala
Friday to conclude a free trade agreement, the Costa Rican Foreign
Trade Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rican officials traveled to Guatemala City Tuesday where
they will discuss with officials from Nicaragua, El Salvador,
Honduras and Guatemala the free trade accord with the Dominican
Republic.
</P>
<P>
The negotiation between the Central American countries and the
Dominican Republic began one year ago but failed to reach a
consensus on the issue. 
</P>
