<HEADLINE> Third Seed Raymond Wins First Rounder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Third-seeded Lisa Raymond
beat Amy Frazier 6-4, 6-2 on Tuesday in the first-round of the
Boston Cup tennis in Massachusetts before the tournament was
suspended due to storms.
</P>
<P>
The suspension came after Mary Joe Fernandez took a 4-1 lead
in the first set of her match against fourth-seeded Silvia Farina
of Italy. The match was to resume Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The tournament was suspended six times today as rains played
havoc with the tournament schedule.
</P>
<P>
In other matches of the day, Nana Miyagi of Japan beat Rachel
McQuillan of Australia 6-4, 6-2, Catalina Cristea of Romania beat
Liezel Horn of South Africa 6-4, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Barbara Schett of Austria beat Kristina Brandi 6-4, 6-0, Elana
Likhoutseva of Russia led Andrea Glass 6-1, 4-2 when the German
retired from the match due to cramps.
</P>
<P>
Megan Shaugnessy beat Nicole Pratt of Australia 6-2, 6-0 and
and Olga Barabanschikova of England beat Erika de Leone 6-1,
6-2. 
</P>
