<HEADLINE> Spanish Police Raid Underground Cocaine Factory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Spanish police have raided an
underground cocaine-processing factory in suburban Madrid and
arrested 12 drug trafficking suspects in the capital and the
Canary Islands.
</P>
<P>
In the raid on the factory located under a villa, police found
nine kilograms of cocaine, large and unknown quantities of raw
materials, two guns and more than 2,000 U.S dollars worth of local
and foreign currencies.
</P>
<P>
Police said the factory had sophisticated drug-producing
equipment.
</P>
<P>
Of those arrested, three major criminal suspects were
identified as Colombians who were said to be responsible for
importing materials from their own country, and getting them
processed in Spain.
</P>
<P>
Their nine collaborators were from Spain, Ghana, Togo, Guinea,
Liberia, South Africa and Colombia, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
