<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployed Aided In Shaanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The provincial government urged
concerned departments to use employment service centers to ensure
the basic life needs of laid-off workers, China Daily reported
today.
</P>
<P>
"By August 20, laid-off workers from enterprises in the
province should be served by re-employment service centers, and by
the end of September, all laid-off workers from State-owned
enterprises should receive services from the centers," said Cheng
Andong, governor of Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 2,000 service centers, established by the local
government and enterprises, are responsible for use relief funds to
help laid-off workers find new jobs.
</P>
<P>
By the end of July, 139,700 of the 455,500 laid-off workers had
found new jobs in Shaanxi.
</P>
<P>
A great number of service centers have been set up in many
parts of China. They hold special training classes for laid-off
workers or provide them information on new jobs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
