<HEADLINE> Italian Cyclists Fail Blood Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The quartet caught of cheating were members of the Mobilvetta
team, namely Paolo Alberati, Graziano Recinelle, Mario Monzoni
and Renzo Ragnetti.
</P>
<P>
The tests, ordered by the International Cycling Union,
detected a higher number of red blood cells than the permitted 50
percent threshold, an indication of the use of the performance
enhancing drug EPO.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the UCI described them "unfit" to continue the
competition in the Tour.
</P>
<P>
