<HEADLINE> Agricultural Machinery Export Grows in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Export of agricultural
machinery will generate 800 million U.S. dollars for Brazil this
year, showing a five-percent growth over that of last year.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian economy daily "Gazeta Mercantil" reported on
Tuesday that exports of farm tractors and harvesters from Brazil
could reach 12,000 units with South American countries being the
main buyers.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, over 10,000 agriculture machines were sold abroad,
which represented a 20 percent growth upon the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The export is expected to grow 163 percent from 304 million
dollars in 1993 to 800 million dollars this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
