<HEADLINE> Nigeria Names New National Soccer Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria has appointed Amodu
Shaibu to restart his coaching stint to head the national soccer
squad, soccer officials said here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This was the second time for Shaibu to coach the national
squad after his first four-year stint was stopped in February
1997.
</P>
<P>
However, Shaibu will work with a foreign manager who will soon
be named as technical adviser, said Nigerian Football Association
spokesman Austin Mgbolo.
</P>
<P>
Mgbolo said Shaibu's return to the national team was part of
plans by the Olympic champions to rebuild after their World Cup
campaign ended in a 4-1 second round defeat by Denmark.
</P>
<P>
From 1994 to 1997, Shaibu, who resigned last week from South
African club Orlando Pirates, has coached Nigeria for seven
losses, one draw and two wins during his first spell of coach.
</P>
<P>
Last week, a three-member Nigerian team returned from Europe
to shortlist five Dutch coaches for the post of adviser. 
</P>
</TEXT>
