<HEADLINE> Rios Beaten by Vacek in ATP Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 11 (Xinhua) -- Top-ranked Marcelo Rios
suffered a humiliating defeat by bowing out of the second
rounder in straight sets at the 2.45 million U.S. dollars ATP
Championship in Mason, Ohio on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean player who regained his short-lived number one
spot in the ATP Tour this week, was defeated by 53rd-ranked
Daniel Vacek of the Czech Republic 6-3, 6-2 in merely 62 minutes
in the night.
</P>
<P>
Rios who just broke away from his American coach second time
in three years, stayed at the baseline in most of the time, hit
numerous returns into the net and watched helplessly as Vacek
repeatedly knocked the ball past him.
</P>
<P>
Vacek broke Rios in the sixth game of the first set and the
third and fifth games of the second set to seal the competition
without much challenge.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Andre Agassi, back in the top 10 for the first time
since January 1997, kept his comeback rolling Tuesday by beating
Nicolas Kiefer of Germany.
</P>
<P>
Pete Sampras, the defending champion and No. 1 seed, was still
idle until Wednesday. 
</P>
