<HEADLINE> Beijing to Host Conference on Scientific, Technological Programs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Beijing will become an
intellectual hot spot when 700 Chinese scholars studying abroad
and their domestic peers attend an academic conference scheduled
for August 20-22.
</P>
<P>
The conference, sponsored by the Chinese Association for
Science and Technology (Cast), will focus on leading-edge
scientific subjects and discussions of technological programs
related to China's economic and social development, according to
today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Reinforcing national strength through science and technology
will be the event's theme, the paper reported.
</P>
<P>
Seminars will deal with information science and
microelectronics, life science and biotechnology, material science
and engineering technology, resource and environmental sciences
and sustainable development technology.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,500 theses have been collected with recommendations
from Cast's nationwide subsidiaries, research institutes, colleges
and universities, enterprises, China's embassies and consulates
and overseas scientific circles, said Zhang Yutai, a senior
official with the Cast.
</P>
<P>
Cast held academic conferences in 1992 and 1995, attracting
1,600 young domestic experts and Chinese scholars studying
abroad.  
</P>
