<HEADLINE> Qingdao to Invest One Billion Yuan in Sewage Treatment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Qingdao, a coastal city in east
China's Shandong Province, will invest 1.3 billion yuan before
year 2000 to improve sewage treatment, according to an official
from the city government.
</P>
<P>
The city plans to build 13 sewage treatment plants. Qingdao has
already built three sewage treatment plants with a total daily
capacity of 120,000 tons of wastewater.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao discharged 180 million tons of sewage last year,
including 97.5 million tons of industrial wastewater.
</P>
<P>
An official from the City Environmental Protection Bureau said
that, since 1993, Qingdao has been establishing sewage treatment
projects, primarily to improve the water quality of Qingdao.
</P>
<P>
In the past two years, Qingdao also invested 380 million yuan
to close and relocate 110 enterprises which were causing severe
water pollution.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that, by year 2000, Qingdao should be able to
reduce its total domestic sewage by 30 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
