<DOCNO> XIE19980812.0294 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1,500 New Insect Species Found in Central Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Some 5,500 species of insects
have been found in central China's Henan Province, and 1,500 of
them have been identified only since 1994, thanks to a three-year
survey of the province.
</P>
<P>
The survey, jointly sponsored by the Insect Society of Henan
Province and the Henan Provincial Quarantine Station of Forest
Pest, aims to built a more detailed data bank of the province's
insects.
</P>
<P>
There are at least 1.5 million species of insects around the
world, and China has an estimated 150,000 species, of which 70,000
species have already been discovered.
</P>
<P>
With an abundance of insects, Henan is estimated to have 15,000
species, but by the year 1994 only some 4,000 species had been
discovered. 
</P>
</TEXT>
