<HEADLINE> Beijing Putting National Theater Designs On Display </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The 44 designs for the National
Grand Theater will be on display in the Museum of the Chinese
Revolution in Beijing from August 9 to 16.
</P>
<P>
Wan Siquan, director of the nation's largest end of the century
cultural project, says the designs were submitted by 36
architectural institutes, 20 of them foreign firms.
</P>
<P>
More than 40,000 people have seen the display and 10,000 wrote
down their opinions, which will be used by an 11-member assessment
committee to select the final three candidates.
</P>
<P>
The theater complex, located on the west side of the Great Hall
of the People in Beijing's Tiananmen Square, will include four
major facilities: an opera theater, a concert hall, a drama
theater, and a performance center. The project will cost about 3.5
billion yuan (420 million U.S. dollars).  
