<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Mountain Lokon Showing Signs of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Mountain Lokon in Indonesia's
North Sulawesi province has been showing signs of increasing
activity over the past few days and the local people have stepped
up their alert against a possible volcanic eruption, the local
press reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chief of the Natural Disaster Coordination Control Task Force
in Tomohon district Tampi told reporters that the volcano has been
spewing thin white clouds from its crater over the past few days
and sulfuric fumes at night.
</P>
<P>
Tampi said he had ordered village heads to monitor the daily
activities of the locals, most of whom are farmers.
</P>
<P>
The 1,689-meter high volcano last erupted in 1991, killing a
Swiss national and prompting the evacuation of 11,000 people.
