<HEADLINE> Philippines' Telephone Company to Float Debt Notes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Long Distance
Telephone Co. (PLDT), the country's largest telephone company, is
planning to issue U.S. dollar or Euro debt securities worth 250
million U.S. dollars in the international market.
</P>
