<HEADLINE> Roma Coach Appears in Drug Hearing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 11 (Xinhua) -- AS Roma coach Zemen on Tuesday was
summoned to a drug hearing chaired by the Italian Olympic
Committee for his allegations that a number of Italian soccer
players have used performance-enhancing drugs.
</P>
<P>
Last week, Zemen, a Czech native, told Espresso that he was
amazed by the quick muscular development of players and they used
"medicines", including Alessandro Del Piero and Gianluca Vialli.
</P>
<P>
Riccardo Agricola, head of Juventus' medical team, denied
administering steriods or other banned substances to his players .
</P>
<P>
"To use steriods would be counter productive in soccer," said
Agricola. "They could cause muscle problems and threaten the at
hletes' health."
</P>
<P>
The Turin club and Del Piero have said they would sue Zemen
for libel.
</P>
<P>
Vialli, a former player of Juventus and currently Chelsea's
player-coach in the English Premier League, called Zeman a
"terrorist trying to destabilize the soccer world." 
</P>
</TEXT>
