<HEADLINE> Van Hooijdonk Put on Transfer List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 11 (Xinhua) -- English premier league club
Nottingham Forest have put Dutch striker Pierre van Hooijdonk
with a price of eight million pounds (about 13.05 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old international has been effectively on strike
in the Netherlands since returning from the World Cup after
claiming Forest had not bought enough quality players to survive
in the premier league following their promotion last season.
</P>
<P>
Forest football director Irving Scholar had flown to the Nether
lands on Monday to try to persuade Van Hooijdonk to stay at the
club for whom he scored 34 goals last season.
</P>
<P>
The Dutchman, who still has four years of his Forest contract
to run, joined the club in March 1997 for 4.5 million pounds
after falling out with Scottish champions Celtic.
</P>
<P>
"It saddens me greatly," said Forest manager Dave Bassett.
"But these days it is the players who hold all the cards."
</P>
<P>
Forest begin their premier league campaign at champions
Arsenal on Monday. 
</P>
