<HEADLINE> IFC Launches Hong Kong Dollar Global Notes Offering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 11 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) Tuesday launched a Hong Kong dollar 1 billion
which is equivalent to 128 million U.S. dollars issue under its
Global Medium Term Note program.
</P>
<P>
The 2-year notes carry an annual coupon of 11.30 percent per
annum and an issue price of 100.30 percent.
</P>
<P>
The lead manager and bookrunner is HSBC Markets and Dao Heng
Bank Limited is co-lead manager. Application will be made to the
Hong Kong Monetary authority for Liquidity Adjustment Facility
Eligibility in order to facilitate repo trading.
</P>
<P>
The latest transaction is the 5th borrowing for the new fiscal
year which began on July 1, 1998, and brings IFC's market
borrowing for fiscal year 1999 to about 459 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
IFC is a member of the World Bank Group, financing private
sector projects in developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
